    "Continue to next scene"
    # [Scene: Inlet — Night of the Storm]
    hide ilias_navarro
    hide maya_kestrel

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_2 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, throbbing bass; sparse percussion like distant heartbeats]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The wind, a different voice now — a pressure that seems to breathe; the slap of surf hitting freshly piled sandbags]

    "You feel it before the radios pick it up: a shifting in the smell, the sea moving with an odd, slow inhalation. Dr. Hana's alert was terse on the channel hours before" "Check seams and anchor points. Unusual low pressure moving up the coast."
    "Etta is there at the inlet's edge, shawl whipping like a banner in an ancient gale. Her hands are caked with the same mud as everyone else's, but she moves with a speed that belies age."
    show etta_muir at left:
        zoom 0.7

    etta_muir "We hold the line here. Keep the southern plugs weighted. Get that child’s playhouse up the bank."
    show maya_kestrel at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_kestrel "On it."
    show ilias_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ilias_navarro "I can check the southeast seam — there's a run in the new geotextile!"

    maya_kestrel "Ilias—"

    ilias_navarro "If it tears, the inlet takes the marsh. I'll bolt a line."

    maya_kestrel "You don't have the anchors—"
    "Ilias Navarro: (His voice cuts off as a sound tears the night: fabric and peat giving way, a noise like a giant tearing a page.) 'Hold—'"

    menu:
        "Run to the southeast seam with whatever you can grab":
            "You snatch a coil of rope, fingers numb, and run. The wind grabs your jacket like an old friend pulling you toward something you both know is dangerous."
        "Stay to coordinate from the inlet's ridge and direct volunteers":
            "You plant your boots and shout instructions, your voice carrying over the storm. Somebody needs to keep eyes on the whole inlet and you are what people look to."

    # --- merge ---
    "The storm forces immediate consequences across the inlet"
    hide etta_muir
    hide maya_kestrel
    hide ilias_navarro

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_3 at full_bg
    "You hold the photos later — edges blurred with rain, faces half-seen in headlights — and count out the miscalculations. Every anchor you couldn't buy is a place you now know by its absence. You mark those places in your notebook like a geometric confession."
    show ilias_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ilias_navarro "We plugged where we could. We saved people. But the seam— it opened faster than we expected."
    show maya_kestrel at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_kestrel "The anchors—"

    ilias_navarro "Would have held longer.' He swallows, looking at the water that just took a shape of your town's memory. 'We can study it. We can catalog and publish and make sure it's not in vain."
    "Your throat tightens. The word 'study' is both a comfort and a knife."

    maya_kestrel "We already published the plans without conditions. We taught them to listen to the sea. We believed people would be enough."

    ilias_navarro "You did the right thing. The right thing doesn't always get you through a night."
    # [Scene: Harborfront | Gray Morning — Aftermath]
    hide ilias_navarro
    hide maya_kestrel

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Sparse piano — each note spaced like slow footfalls]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The low, continuous swell of the sea; distant calls; the hum of engines loading up]
    "You stand on the slick planked harborfront, the coral pendant resting against the bone at the base of your throat. Salt tastes bitter on your tongue. Families move past with the careful economy of people who"
    "wrap precious things slowly: heirlooms, a patched sweater, a box of shells. Some faces you know already are hollowed by a small, private courage."
    "Etta approaches, hands balled behind her back, voice flattened like weathered rope."
    show etta_muir at left:
        zoom 0.7

    etta_muir "You held to the town's hand. You told them the truth as it is. People know what they lost because they were told the truth in time to pack something that mattered."
    show maya_kestrel at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_kestrel "They've lost more than anything our protocol could protect. The anchors—"
    "Etta studies you like sea glass."

    etta_muir "You didn't choose the storm. You chose how we face it. That matters."
    "You should feel that as balm. Instead a hollow grows under your sternum — for the fisheries, for the child's playhouse, for the families piling belongings into an anonymous van."
    "From somewhere down the quay you hear a voice that makes your chest constrict, low and uncertain."
    show ilias_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ilias_navarro "I have an offer. A fellowship to quantify what went wrong across three coasts. They want the data, the failures, everything. It's a place to... make more than a report. To scale understanding."
    "You feel the room tilt. This is not unfamiliar territory — him offering a way out to fix the pattern at a scale you could only dream of. It feels like being handed a map that takes him away."

    ilias_navarro "I thought I could do both. But the timeline they'd give me would take me from here for a long while. They'll fund a team, equipment. They said they'd support the people we've already helped if I take it."
    "You try to hold the pain from showing. The town needs him in the slow, patient way it needs hands. But the world outside wants the failures cataloged. You remember the nights of calculating risk, the ledger closing and opening like a mouth."

    ilias_navarro "I'm not abandoning what we started. I promise you that. I want to make sure our mistakes teach others — not just here, but where no one else will have them first."

    maya_kestrel "Promise me you'll come back if you can."

    ilias_navarro "I promise. But I can't promise the timeline."
    hide etta_muir
    hide maya_kestrel
    hide ilias_navarro

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_5 at full_bg
    "You count — not spreadsheets this time, but moments. The picnic that didn't happen yet, the unpatched floor, the lab notes in his waterproof sleeve. Each one becomes a kind of ledger all its own."
    show ilias_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ilias_navarro "Take care of them."
    show maya_kestrel at right:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_kestrel "Keep your hands steady, wherever you go."

    ilias_navarro "I'll try."
    "Etta stands with you, both of you watching the van's taillights disappear down the quay."
    show etta_muir at center:
        zoom 0.7

    etta_muir "People go. People come. Some of the things that leave take pieces of us to fix places they've no business mending."
    "You press your thumb against the carved coral — the coolness anchors you. The pendant had been an heirloom; now it feels like a ledger you carry on your skin."

    maya_kestrel "We rose. We built what we could with our hands. We were honest with the town. That honesty... it wasn't enough tonight."

    etta_muir "No. But it will be the story people tell. They'll know they were given a try."
    "You look at the harbor, at the boats bobbing and the quiet snap of ropes. You hold the photos in your open notebook — the torn playhouse, the empty nets, the faces of people who will"
    "leave and those who will stay with a new, harder kind of courage. You catalogue the missteps in margins and blot them with tears you don't let fall."
    hide ilias_navarro
    hide maya_kestrel
    hide etta_muir

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: One slow note resolves into nothing, leaving the world to exhale]
    "You stand a long time, the pendant warm now from your touch. The rise had been real. For a while there had been sun in the gutters and green in the trays and a map you"
    "could read like truth. The fall is absolute tonight — a seam ripped open at a child's playhouse, fisheries claimed, neighbors loading up boxes and leaving with the last of the tide."
    "You do not have easy answers. You have only the work you did, the people who still look to you with something like hope, and a notebook full of photographs and plans and places you miscalculated."
    "You fold the notebook closed, the leather creaking like a hinge that has been opened too often. You tuck it against your ribs, against the place where guilt and care live together."
    # [Scene: Harborfront | Dusk]
    "The town moves; some leave, some stay, and the sea continues with an old indifference."
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fade to low, empty sustain]
